From ecad6db1d6db7db977412916d438e16113963e81 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Karthikeya <karthi@jovio.in>
Date: Mon, 29 Jun 2026 08:23:16 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 4/4] feat(outbound): TRAI-aware campaign MVP (Growth + Scale
 plans)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Outbound calling is delicate in India because TRAI's TCCCPR-2018
fines hit ₹25k-₹50k PER VIOLATION for calling DND-registered numbers.
The schema and dispatcher are designed defensively:

SCHEMA — supabase/006_outbound_campaigns.sql
  outbound_campaigns:
    - calling-window enforcement (window_start / window_end IST,
      defaults 10:00-19:00)
    - max_concurrent capped at 25 hardware ceiling
    - status state machine: draft -> running -> paused/completed/cancelled
  outbound_recipients:
    - dnd_blocked flag + scrubbed_at timestamp
    - consent_call_id FK pointing back to the original inbound call
      that requested a callback (consent proof = DND exempt)
    - status state machine: pending -> scrubbing -> queued/blocked_dnd
      -> in_progress -> completed/failed
  outbound_opt_outs:
    - tenant-level DNC list, populated via STOP SMS / in-call request
    - checked on every recipient INSERT (filtered out before queueing)

API — api-server/src/outbound.ts (mounted via mountOutboundRoutes)
  POST /api/campaigns                       create draft
  POST /api/campaigns/:id/recipients        bulk-upload (max 10k/req)
                                            normalises phone to +91 E.164
                                            cross-references opt_outs
                                            keeps consent_call_id link
  POST /api/campaigns/:id/start             flip to running
  POST /api/campaigns/:id/pause             flip to paused
  POST /api/campaigns/:id/opt-out           add phone to tenant DNC
                                            + mark pending rows as opted_out
  GET  /api/campaigns/:id/stats             status counters for dashboard

  All endpoints write audit_log entries.

DISPATCHER — api-server/src/jobs/outbound-dispatcher.ts
  Long-running worker polling every 30s. For each running campaign,
  enforces:
    1. IST calling-window check
    2. max_concurrent slot accounting
    3. DND scrubbing on 'pending' (currently a STUB — fails SAFE
       blocking the number if DND_SCRUB_PROVIDER_URL is unset).
       Wire Exotel / TRAI NCPR feed here before launching to numbers
       without consent_call_id.
    4. Dispatch via POST /outbound to voice-pipeline (which applies
       the TRAI AI-disclosure on connect — already in main.py)
    5. Retry up to 3 attempts with 24h backoff on dispatch failure
    6. Auto-complete campaign when no more pending/queued/in-progress

  Runs as jovio-outbound-dispatcher.service — single instance for now
  (multi-instance dispatching needs row locking via
  SELECT FOR UPDATE SKIP LOCKED — future enhancement).

WHAT'S DELIBERATELY MISSING and needs follow-up:
  - Dashboard UI for campaign creation (next round if needed)
  - Real DND scrub provider integration (Exotel API or TRAI direct)
  - voice-pipeline /outbound endpoint (separate change)
  - STOP-SMS opt-out webhook handler (depends on Wati SMS plan)
